---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { providers } from "../lib/site";
---

<Base
  title="Troubleshooting · Cloud Speech for Chrome"
  description="Fixes for common Cloud Speech for Chrome extension problems: no audio, missing voices, keyboard shortcuts, and unexpected charges."
  root="../"
  active="troubleshooting"
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12">
    <p><a class="link text-sm text-stone-600" href="../">← Home</a></p>

    <header class="mt-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Troubleshooting</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
        Fixes for problems in the extension itself. Provider errors like invalid credentials
        or access denied are covered in each setup guide. If none of these help, please
        <a class="link" href="https://github.com/vivswan/cloud-speech-for-chrome/issues"
          >open an issue on GitHub</a
        >
        with the provider you're using and what you tried.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">No audio plays</h2>
      <div class="card mt-3 p-5">
        <ul
          class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700 marker:text-stone-400"
        >
          <li>Check your browser and system audio settings (volume, muted tab, output device)</li>
          <li>Confirm other audio (e.g. a YouTube video) plays in the browser</li>
          <li>
            Check the mini-player; playback may be paused, or a previous read may still be in the
            queue (right-click → <strong>Stop</strong> to clear it)
          </li>
          <li>Try a short, plain-text selection to rule out very long or unusual content</li>
          <li>Restart Chrome; extensions occasionally need a fresh service worker</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Voices missing after an update</h2>
      <div class="card mt-3 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
          If the voice list is empty or your saved voice disappeared after the extension updated,
          the cached voice list just needs a refresh: open <strong>Settings</strong>, go to your
          provider, and click <strong>Save &amp; test</strong> again. The extension re-fetches the
          voices and your favorites reappear.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Keyboard shortcuts don't work</h2>
      <div class="card mt-3 p-5">
        <ul
          class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700 marker:text-stone-400"
        >
          <li>
            The defaults are <kbd>Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+S</kbd> (read aloud) and
            <kbd>Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+E</kbd> (download); another extension may have claimed them
          </li>
          <li>
            Review and rebind them at <span class="value">chrome://extensions/shortcuts</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Unexpected charges</h2>
      <div class="card mt-3 p-5">
        <ul
          class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700 marker:text-stone-400"
        >
          <li>
            Every character, including spaces, counts toward usage; long pages add up quickly
          </li>
          <li>
            Premium tiers cost much more: neural voices are ~4× standard, and generative,
            long-form, and HD voices more still; see the
            <a class="link" href="../pricing/">pricing comparison</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            Monitor usage in your provider's console (AWS Console → Polly → usage reports, Azure
            Portal metrics, Google Cloud billing, OpenAI usage dashboard)
          </li>
          <li>Set up billing alerts or budgets so you're warned early</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Provider errors</h2>
      <div class="card mt-3 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
          If <strong>Save &amp; test</strong> reports "These credentials didn't work", or playback
          fails with a "Speech synthesis failed" banner followed by the provider's own error
          message, the cause depends on your provider. Each setup guide has a troubleshooting
          section for them:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {
            providers.map((provider) => (
              <a
                class="tap flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-stone-200 px-3 py-1.5 text-sm text-stone-700 transition-colors hover:border-stone-400 hover:text-ink"
                href={`../setup/${provider.id}/`}
              >
                <span class={`h-2 w-2 rounded-full ${provider.dot}`} />
                {provider.name}
              </a>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-amber-900">Still stuck?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-amber-900/90">
        Report bugs and ask questions on
        <a
          class="font-medium underline decoration-amber-900/40 underline-offset-2"
          href="https://github.com/vivswan/cloud-speech-for-chrome/issues">GitHub Issues</a
        >. Include your provider, the exact error message, and the steps to reproduce. Never
        include your API keys.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
